  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Archi Coordinator",
  "description": "<h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><p><strong>Design & Technical Coordination</strong></p><ul><li>Review and coordinate architectural drawings, shop drawings, and specifications</li><li>Identify design conflicts and liaise with consultants and contractors for resolution</li><li>Ensure compliance with project design intent and construction standards</li></ul><p><strong>Project Support</strong></p><ul><li>Monitor progress of architectural works on-site and report deviations</li><li>Assist in preparing method statements, technical reports, and schedules</li><li>Support site inspections and quality control activities</li></ul><p><strong>Documentation & Records</strong></p><ul><li>Maintain records of drawings, revisions, and approvals</li><li>Assist in the preparation of as-built drawings and handover documentation</li><li>Ensure compliance with local building codes and regulations</li></ul><p><strong>Team Collaboration</strong></p><ul><li>Coordinate with MEP, structural, and other disciplines</li><li>Attend project coordination meetings and provide technical input</li><li>Support senior architectural staff in design optimization and value engineering initiatives</li></ul><h3>Qualifications & Experience</h3><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Architecture or related field</li><li>3–5 years of experience in construction projects</li><li>Knowledge of architectural drawings, specifications, and construction methods</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
